        <h2 class="underline"><span>Who</span></h2>

        <p>The Gospel Center Lausanne is a member of the <a target="_blank"
                                                            href="http://www.evangelique.ch">Réseau évangélique
                suisse</a> (Swiss evangelical network), of the <a target="_blank" href="http://www.lafree.ch">Fédération
                romande des Églises évangéliques</a> (the swiss federation of French-speaking evangelical churches) and
            is linked to the <a
                    target="_blank"
                    href="http://www.gospel-wave.org">Gospel Wave movement.</a></p>

        <h2 class="underline"><span>How</span></h2>

        <p>The Gospel Center has the desire to live the Gospel in the most relevant way, also in the area of healing and
            miracles.</p>

        <p>The Gospel Center envisions a communication through modern technology in order to impact people in their
            everyday lives. Our audiovisual media as well as our set of activities pursue this aim.</p>

        <p>We are convinced that there are various ways of living out the Christian life, while simple moments of life
            shared together are just as enriching. Our Sunday evening celebrations are just one way of living out this
            Christian lifestyle.</p>

        <h2 class="underline"><span>Why</span></h2>

        <p>The Gospel Center exists to stimulate, develop and reveal a positive, practical and powerful way of living
            based on Jesus through the Bible. We believe that the Christian life is more than just Sunday celebrations
            and church programs, but it is also lived out during the rest of the week, in our various activities as well
            as our workplaces.</p>

        <p>The Gospel Center wishes to offer an environment where fellowship is a key element. An environment where the
            faith of everyone can grow in a healthy and balanced way as much in the doing than in the being. We desire
            to see God move through miracles, healings and transformed lives.</p>

        <h2 class="underline"><span>Structure</span></h2>

        <p>The Gospel Center works for and through its “bases”, groups of 4 to 7 people based on geographical area and
            interests. The aim is to offer places of reasonable size to develop relationships and spiritual growth. The
            ”bases” focus as much on shared activities (sports, excursions, cultural activities, etc.) as on time spent
            in and around the Bible. The Gospel Center wants to offer the possibility to each and every one to get
            involved according to his/her abilities, time and motivation in the life of the ”bases” and from there in
            the various church activities such as the Sunday evening celebrations.</p>

        <h2 class="underline"><span>Finances</span></h2>

        <p>The Gospel Center Lausanne receives no government support and is a non-profit organization. All the running
            costs are being covered by the free commitment of everyone. Our accounts are approved by the General
            Assembly after having been checked by a trustee.</p>

